            <h5 class="card-title">OOP Study Planner System</h5>

            <p class="card-text">
              Developed a Python console application simulating a real-world study planner for students.<br>
              Leveraged object-oriented programming (OOP) principles including encapsulation, class design, and object collaboration.<br>
              Demonstrated initiative to learn advanced OOP concepts beyond the academic syllabus.<br>
            </p>

            <strong>Key Features:</strong>
            <ul>
                <li>Create and manage tasks with titles, descriptions, deadlines, and status</li>
                <li>Mark tasks as completed and detect overdue tasks automatically</li>
                <li>Schedule, update, and cancel study sessions for tasks</li>
                <li>Prioritize tasks based on subject priority, completion status, and deadlines</li>
                <li>Automatically suggest study sessions for unscheduled tasks</li>
                <li>Display structured task lists and study schedules</li>
            </ul>
            </ul>

            <p class="card-text">
              <strong>Tech Stack: </strong><br>
              Language: Python 3.x <br>
              Paradigm: Object-Oriented Programming<br>
              Core Concepts: Encapsulation, Object Collaboration, Class Design, Utility Methods<br>
              Libraries Used: datetime (for managing deadlines and reminders) and Standard Python Built-Ins<br>
            </p>

