            <h5 class="card-title">Node.JS Library Management System</h5>

            <p class="card-text">
             This project is a full-stack web application developed as part of a group assignment using Node.js, Express, EJS, and MySQL.<br>
              The system supports core functionalities such as user authentication, role-based access control (RBAC), and management of entities including publishers, books, and users.<br><br>

              I was responsible for designing and implementing the Publisher Management module, which includes full CRUD (Create, Read, Update, Delete) operations with database integration and server-side rendering using EJS.<br>
              The module also includes a search functionality that allows users to filter publishers by name, address, or country using keyword-based queries.<br><br>
              I collaborated with teammate to integrate the existing role-based access control system into the Publisher module by applying middleware and session-based role checks to restrict create, update, and delete actions to admin users.
            </p>

            
             <strong>Key Features:</strong>
                <ul>
                  <li>Full CRUD functionality for publisher management (create, view, update, delete).</li>
                  <li>Database integration using MySQL for persistent publisher data storage.</li>
                  <li>Server-side rendering using EJS for dynamic page rendering.</li>
                  <li>Collaboration with teammate to integrate existing RBAC into the Publisher module.</li>
                  <li>Admin-only access enforcement for create, update, and delete operations using middleware checks.</li>
                  <li>Conditional UI rendering in EJS based on user role.</li>
                  <li>Search functionality for filtering publishers by name, address, and country using keyword-based queries.</li>
                </ul>

            <p class="card-text">
              <strong>Tech Stack: </strong><br>
              Language: JavaScript (Node.Js) <br>
              Backend Framework: Express.js<br>
              Template Engine: EJS (Server-Side Rendering)<br>
              Database: MySQL<br>
              Hosting/Deployment: Filess.io (Database Hosting) and Render (Web App Hosting)<br>
            </p>

